The artistry is extremely subtle, and without a solid grasp of theoretical Neo-Dadaism most of the symbolism will go over a typical viewer‚Äôs head. There‚Äôs also Blueno‚Äôs absurdist outlook, which is deftly woven into his characterisation- his personal philosophy draws heavily from postmodern literature, for instance. The fans understand this stuff; they have the intellectual capacity to truly appreciate the depths of these references, to realise that they‚Äôre not just funny- they say something deep about LIFE. As a consequence people who dislike Blueno truly ARE idiots- of course they wouldn‚Äôt appreciate, for instance, the humour in Blueno‚Äôs existential catchphrase ‚Äúüí°,‚Äù which itself is a cryptic reference to Eric Carle‚Äôs American epic Brown Bear, Brown Bear, What Do You See. Many people always ask me how I was able to get into Alpert Medical School as a 16 year old who skipped 3 grades of high school. They think I got in because of my scholarly records, but no the key is the interview.
As I sat in the Dean's office in front of the board of reviewers for my application, the Dean asks me "Why should you be a good candidate for this medical school?" They seemed bored but I replied "Well I was born a child prodigy, placed 1st in my state spelling bee for three consecutive years, I can speak eight different languages not counting Latin, play four different instruments, I skipped grades 4 through 6, and graduated my high school as valedictorian at the age of 14. I then worked as an intern at both Telsa, and NASA." Suddenly the room burst into laughter and many of board instantly started scribbling down "No" near the application check marks. The Dean says "Sorry but you are just not the type we are looking for." But then I said "Excuse me but I wasn't finished... I went to Brown for undergrad" The Dean looked at me like an idiot and said "So....?" Then I replied with a smile "And I was a PLME" An audible gasp let out by the board was so loud the secretary had to come in. You could hear a pin drop and then suddenly all at once the entire board clicked their pens on the "Approved Box" and I was instantly handed a diploma and now I'm teaching advanced physicals there. I guess you can say I'm pretty smart.
